<TITLE> Nephew kills aunt </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gazipur, May 8 (bdnews24.com) An aunt was chopped to death and the uncle injured by their nephew on Saturday morning. The dead is Rehana Akthar, 35, wife of Billal Hossain, 40, of Hyedrabad village of Gazipur Sadr upazila. The incident occurred when the nephew Ismail Hossain had a hot exchange with his aunt at around 7am. Ismail used to stay at his uncle's house. Md Abdul Karim, a sub-inspector of the Pubail Police Camp under the Joydebpur Police Station, said that Ismail had an altercation with his aunt when she threw dirty water out into the yard. At one stage he chopped Rehana with a sharp implement (locally known as 'boti') and also beat his uncle when he came to save his wife. The relatives took Rehana to the Dhaka Medical College Hospital at around 9am where the duty doctor declared her dead. Billal was admitted to the Gazipur Sadr Hospital. Ismail fled the scene when the locals chased him. Gazipur's assistant police superintendent Md Akhtaruzzaman and the Joydebpur Police Station's OC Abdur Rashid visited the spot at around 10.30am. bdne
